            <bug_when>2009-02-23 10:38:57 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>Quote by Sebastian:

&quot;Instead of defining a boot part and configuring it to be the boot part, it may be better to keep the include list for the boot process outside the other declaration. As there is no package boot then anymore. The boot part is automatically loaded and this at least includes the application class and qx.core.Package.&quot;

I fully agree with this statement. The include list of the normal application already defines the boot part. The user should only have to define the &quot;non-boot&quot; parts explicitly in the config files.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
